<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/output.css">
    <title>Error – URL Shortener</title>
</head>

<body class="font-mono bg-taupe-950 flex flex-col items-center text-mauve-400 min-h-screen">
    <nav class="flex flex-row justify-between h-fit items-center border-dashed border-b w-full">
        <div class="text-5xl font-extrabold p-3">URL shortener</div>
        <div class="px-4">Profile</div>
    </nav>

    <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center flex-1 gap-4 text-center px-4">
        <div class="text-9xl font-extrabold opacity-20 tracking-tighter select-none">400</div>

        <div class="border border-dashed border-mauve-400 px-4 py-1 text-xs tracking-widest opacity-60">
            bad request
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-xl font-semibold">url is required</h1>

        <hr class="border-dashed border-mauve-400 opacity-30 w-10">

        <p class="text-sm opacity-50 leading-relaxed">
            the request body is missing a
            <code class="border border-dashed border-mauve-400 px-1 opacity-80">url</code>
            field.<br>
            please provide a valid url to shorten.
        </p>

        <a href="/"
            class="border border-mauve-400 px-4 py-1 text-sm bg-taupe-800 hover:cursor-pointer rounded-md mt-2">
            ← go back
        </a>
    </div>
</body>

</html>
